<subSubSection box="[199,1055,730,754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">For a reader’s convenience, the amended Fraser’s key to males of the species of</subSubSection>
<emphasis box="[1063,1136,731,754]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
<subSubSection box="[1063,1132,731,754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="nomenclature">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1063,1132,731,754]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lestes</taxonomicName>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Selys, 1862" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1143,1390,730,754]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Platylestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1259,730,754]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Platylestes</emphasis>
Selys, 1862
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fraser, 1951" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1951" box="[151,408,766,790]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Sinhalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,271,766,790]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Sinhalestes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser, F. C." box="[277,408,766,790]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="61 - 69" refId="ref5002" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1951) Outline of a new classification for the legion Lestes Selys (Order Odonata). Entomological News, 60 (2), 61 - 69." type="journal article" year="1951">Fraser, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[443,500,766,790]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[510,603,766,790]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[613,719,766,790]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[729,853,766,790]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[904,1008,766,790]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
is reproduced below entirely (in spite of the lack or scarce new information on some species). The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1951" box="[847,967,802,826]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Sinhalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[847,967,802,826]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Sinhalestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser, F. C." box="[1179,1324,802,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="61 - 69" refId="ref5002" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1951) Outline of a new classification for the legion Lestes Selys (Order Odonata). Entomological News, 60 (2), 61 - 69." type="journal article" year="1951">Fraser (1951)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Hagen in Selys, 1862" authorityName="Hagen in Selys" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes orientalis</emphasis>
Hagen in Selys, 1862
</taxonomicName>
after publication of his monograph (
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser, F. C." box="[866,997,838,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refId="ref4932" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1933) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Odonata. Vol. I. Taylor and Francis, London, 423 pp." type="book" year="1933">Fraser 1933</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Selys, 1891" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1891" box="[1014,1320,838,862]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis box="[1014,1191,838,862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes bilineatus</emphasis>
Selys, 1891
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmidt, 1964" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes malaisei</emphasis>
Schmidt, 1964
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[578,683,874,898]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, are not included as most probably belonging to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fraser, 1922" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1922" box="[1192,1436,874,898]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Indolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1192,1300,874,898]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Indolestes</emphasis>
Fraser, 1922
</taxonomicName>
(see, respectively, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[349,525,910,934]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="229 - 256" refId="ref5230" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1960) On the identity of some little known southeast Asiatic Odonata in European museums described by De Selys Longchamps. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 38, 229 - 256." type="journal article" year="1960">Lieftinck (1960)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kosterin, O. E." box="[578,760,910,934]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="561 - 575" refId="ref5092" refString="Kosterin, O. E. (2018) Rediscovery of Lestes nigriceps Fraser, 1924 (Odonata: Lestidae) in eastern Cambodia. Zootaxa, 4526 (4), 561 - 575. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4526.4.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Kosterin (2018))</bibRefCitation>
. Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys Apices" authorityYear="1891" box="[830,937,910,934]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodalis">
<emphasis box="[830,937,910,934]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. nodalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(occurring at least in Lower 
<collectingCountry box="[1249,1354,910,934]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Lahiri" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. garoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are included. The volume and limits of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[786,902,946,970]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Platylestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[786,902,946,970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Platylestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear and the attribution of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hagen in Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1301,1427,947,970]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praemorsus">
<emphasis box="[1301,1427,947,970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">praemorsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group to either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[318,385,983,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[318,385,983,1006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[423,539,982,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Platylestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[423,539,982,1006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Platylestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is equivocal (
<bibRefCitation author="Kosterin, O. E." box="[691,850,982,1006]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="561 - 575" refId="ref5092" refString="Kosterin, O. E. (2018) Rediscovery of Lestes nigriceps Fraser, 1924 (Odonata: Lestidae) in eastern Cambodia. Zootaxa, 4526 (4), 561 - 575. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4526.4.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Kosterin 2018</bibRefCitation>
); here they are referred to in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1167,1234,983,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1167,1234,983,1006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
just in accordance with the current practice. Also I abstain from inclusion of subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hagen in Selys, 1862" authorityName="Hagen in Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[934,1373,1018,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praemorsus">
<emphasis box="[934,1134,1019,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes praemorsus</emphasis>
Hagen in Selys, 1862
</taxonomicName>
since this matter is insufficiently resolved. The measurement ranges for 
<taxonomicName authority="Fraser, 1923" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1923" box="[858,1166,1054,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorothea">
<emphasis box="[858,1027,1054,1078]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes dorothea</emphasis>
Fraser, 1923
</taxonomicName>
are given as extended by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lahiri, A. R." box="[151,298,1090,1114]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="1 - 402" refId="ref5140" refString="Lahiri, A. R. (1987) Studies on the odonate fauna of Meghalaya. Records of the Zoological Survey of India, Miscellaneous publication, Occasional paper No. 99, 1 - 402." type="book chapter" year="1987">Lahiri (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. Fraser’s “thorax” is replaced by a more correct “synthorax”. Fraser’s statement “Thorax immaculate” for 
<taxonomicName authority="Selys, 1891" authorityName="Selys Apices" authorityYear="1891" box="[151,433,1126,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodalis">
<emphasis box="[151,303,1126,1150]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes nodalis</emphasis>
Selys, 1891
</taxonomicName>
contradicts his own description of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser, F. C." box="[941,1070,1126,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refId="ref4932" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1933) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Odonata. Vol. I. Taylor and Francis, London, 423 pp." type="book" year="1933">Fraser 1933</bibRefCitation>
) and corrected to “Synthorax with few black spots”.
</subSubSection>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[151,1436,1229,1280]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">1. Synthorax without metallic markings ...................................................................... 2</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[226,1436,1287,1309]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Synthorax with green metallic antehumeral stripes........................................................... 6</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[151,1436,1317,1368]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">2. Pterostigma unicolorous................................................................................ 3</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[226,1436,1375,1397]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Pterostigma bicolorous................................................................................ 4</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
3. No broad black dorsal stripe on synthorax (middorsal carina can be finely stressed with black); occiput reddish brown to creamy white; paraprocts extend at most to 1/3 of expanded part of cerci................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hag. Synthorax" authorityName="Hag. Synthorax" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concinnus">
<emphasis box="[1262,1384,1464,1485]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. concinnus</emphasis>
Hag. 
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
Synthorax with a broad black dorsal stripe; occiput mat black; paraprocts extend to the end of expanded part of cerci.............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Fras." authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1924" box="[1282,1437,1522,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patricia">
<emphasis box="[1282,1383,1523,1544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. patricia</emphasis>
Fras.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[151,1437,1551,1603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
4. Synthorax with about 10 small black spots on each side; pterostigma white at both ends.............. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ramb. Synthorax" authorityName="Ramb. Synthorax" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Platylestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platystylus">
<emphasis box="[1241,1367,1581,1602]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">P. platystylus</emphasis>
Ramb. 
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Synthorax (in mature individuals) with few black spots; pterostigma with its costal third palest brown, posterior two thirds dark brown.............................................................................................. 5</paragraph>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[151,1436,1668,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
5. Apices of cerci rounded, of their inner margins blunt............................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Selys Apices" authorityName="Selys Apices" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodalis">
<emphasis box="[1282,1379,1698,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. nodalis</emphasis>
Selys 
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[226,1437,1727,1749]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
Apices of cerci and their inner inflations strongly pointed....................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Lahiri" authorityName="in Lahiri" authorityYear="1987" box="[1254,1437,1727,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garoensis">
<emphasis box="[1254,1371,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. garoensis</emphasis>
Lahiri
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[151,1436,1757,1808]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">6. Synthorax with a uniform narrow antehumeral stripe on each side.............................................. 7</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[226,1436,1815,1837]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Synthorax with narrow antehumeral stripes expanded outwardly at the upper side.................................. 9</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[226,1436,1845,1867]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Synthorax with antehumeral stripes deeply scalloped or crenulate on the outer sides............................... 10</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[226,1436,1874,1896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Synthorax with the whole of dorsum and forepart of sides briliant metallic green................................. 10</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[151,1437,1907,1983]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,1961,2040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
7. Vertex of head metallic green; thorax largely black; only 11 postnodal nervures to fore-wings............ 
<taxonomicName authority="Fras." authorityName="Fras." box="[1266,1437,1961,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angularis">
<emphasis box="[1266,1383,1961,1982]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. angularis</emphasis>
Fras.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1961,2040]" box="[226,1436,1990,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Vertex of head non-metallic; 12 to 14 postnodal nervures fore-wings............................................ 8</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1961,2040]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,153,527]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
8. Vertex of head pale brown; dorsum of thorax pale brown, with very prominent brilliant metallic green antehumeral stripes; 12 postnodal nervures to fore-wings........................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Ramb." authorityName="Ramb." box="[1256,1437,183,205]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridulus">
<emphasis box="[1256,1367,183,204]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">L. viridulus</emphasis>
Ramb.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,527]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">
Vertex of head mat black; dorsum of thorax black with an obscure narrow metallic green stripe on each side; 14 postnodal nervures to fore-wings.................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Fras." authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1924" box="[1268,1437,242,263]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis box="[1268,1383,242,263]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">L. nigriceps</emphasis>
Fras.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,527]" box="[151,1437,271,322]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">
9. Sides of thorax pale brown with a few black points................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Hag. Sides" authorityName="Hag. Sides" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elatus">
<emphasis box="[1302,1384,300,322]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">L. elatus</emphasis>
Hag. 
